race.comment: CALLENEM THRU (3) started in the red here first-up and was beaten a whisker from a wide gate. Map better today and Ford goes on. The Sydney barn targets this venue and with the extra fitness she can make amends. SINGLE BEAT (8) is a local who had been close up here her last three. Has been kept on the fresh side and Jack Martin replaces the apprentice. The shorter sprint suits and she always puts in.  RILEYCAT (6) resumes and showed plenty early doors. She was narrowly beaten in a recent Goulburn trial suggesting she's back on track. Day rides and look for her to be finishing hard. PROPHET TIME (10) surprised the market narrowly beaten here last time. Maps for a soft run and is in the mix with Penza sticking.
